The employers are the Metropolitan Transportation Authority and its subsidiaries, the New York City Transit Authority and the Manhattan and Bronx Surface Transit Operating Authority.

The primary union is Local 100 of the Transport Workers Union, which represents 34,400 employees, from bus drivers and motormen to token collectors and car cleaners.

John E. Lawe is its president. Two locals of the Amalgamated Transit Union represent 2,300 bus drivers and mechanics in Queens and Staten Island.

ISSUES - Management has offered wage increases of 2 percent in each year of a 3-year contract. The Transport Workers Union has asked for 10 percent increases in the 1st and 11th months of a 20-month contract.